com.asqueados.vpm.entities
Class Personage

java.lang.Object
  com.asqueados.vpm.entities.Personage

public class Personage
extends java.lang.Object

Class that encapsulates a character A character has traits. You can set and query for them Notice: I wanted to name this class "Character" but this is a default java class which brings a lot of troubles. Class is renamed as "Personage" but data files will still use "character".

Author:
Pablo J. Urbano Santos

setValue

public void setValue(java.lang.String traitName,
                     java.lang.Object value)
If the character has a trait with name traitName, it sets its value to value. Otherwise, it tries to create a new Trait with that value, guessing the type. If the type can't be guessed, the character is unmodified.
